This interface covers most of the reportable telemetry types for most of the APMs tools I've seen in the marked. A provider can be an APM tool/product where Orleans should post the telemetry data like for example [NewRelic](http://newrelic.com), Azure Application Insights, App Dynamics, DataDogHQ, etc., platform performance counters (on Windows regular performance counters, on Linux its own logd etc), a live even ingestion system like Azure EventHubs, or just a cold storage for metrics like a SQL Database, DocumentDb, Azure Table storage, whatever. The idea with the provider is to receive the telemetry incoming from Orleans clusters and store/process the way it usually does it.

The intention with the provider is to **report** telemetry data and not to analyze and neither parse telemetry. It behaves just as a proxy from the data coming from Orleans and the underlying APM Tool/storage APIs.

**Provider registration/configuration**

The providers should be registered using reflection and loaded at Silo startup. The configuration should be made by regular Orleans XML config, or by Orleans configuration objects in order to keep the config experience seamless with the other system components like Storage Providers for example. There can be multiple `ITelemetryProvider` registrations so all should post the telemetry to its underlying implementations in parallel e.g., you want the data to go to Event Viewer, Performance Counter and a SQL Database for different kinds of analysis. 

**Telemetry Consumer - System Grain (the "Consumer")**

This grain behave as a consumer from a internal stream where all the telemetry reported by Orleans is pushed from the producer (more on that later) and will forward the telemetry request to all the registered `ITelemetryProvider` providers in order push the telemetry forward to the underlying APM Tool/storage.

**Telemetry Manager - Proxy (the "Producer")**

One concrete **internal** class that behaves as a proxy for the telemetry providers. This class should implement the `ITelemetryProvider` interface in order to expose the same methods to be consumed by Orleans Runtime components so key measurable/critical points on Orleans infrastructure can be measured as KPIs.

This Proxy is responsible for receive the Telemetry and push this request to the stream in a **Fire & Forget** async model so there is no wait time during the regular process of a Grain method call (for example), since it is not a critical component for the actual request and should not impact its behavior. This class should be accessible internally by all Orleans infrastructure and from the `Grain`-based classes as well (more on that later).

**Custom metrics? Oh yeah!**

Most of the APM tools besides regular/common performance counters like requests p/ second, CPU, Memory, I/O, etc., also gives its users the ability to push their own technical and business metrics for further analysis, we should provide that ability for Orleans developers as well! 

The implementation of the _Telemetry Manager_ is internal to Orleans Runtime however, `ITelemetryProvider` is publicly available for Grain developers from the `Grain` class. This allow them to push custom telemetry just the same way as we do internally within Orleans framework boundaries. 


